The paper deals with activity classification using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance gain on the model and what the model has learned, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of synthetic images, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a tool that can help study model and dataset design, which could also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
